Package com.chillycheesy.modulo.commands.operator

Class Operation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.chillycheesy.modulo.commands.operator.Operation
  • public class Operation
extends java.lang.Object
    An operation wad created when OperatorFinder finds a valid operator.

    The operation is responsible for parsing the operator and determining the next command flow.

      • buildFormRegex

        public static Operation buildFormRegex​(CommandFlow flux,
                                       java.lang.String regex,
                                       OperatorListener listener)
        Create an Operation from a CommandFlow. The operator is represented by a regex. When the method find a match it will create an Operation. The left part is before the regex match, the center part is the match, and the right part is after the match. The regex is modified by the method for escaping skip characters. The operator is escape when:
        • We found a '\' before the operator.
        • The operator is between parentheses.
        • The operator is between brackets.
        • The operator is between curly braces.
        Parameters:
        flux - The CommandFlow to parse.
        regex - The regex to match.
        listener - The operation listener.
        Returns:
        The Operation.
